Ask HN: Explain P != NP in plain english
text:
Could someone explain P != NP to me like I'm literally five :-)

What is P? What is NP?

Why and what part of it is nondeterministic and deterministic? How does verification play into it?

Does this only apply to decision (yes/no) problems or can it be other problems?

What does an equal to and not equal to relationship mean? Why does it matter?

Also what is NP-Hard? What is NP-Complete?

Thank you!
